<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">385</span> - <span property="pageEnd">402</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19325055/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19325055</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.292085123">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FNH+%3D+focal+nodular+hyperplasia&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FNH = focal nodular hyperplasia</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=Gd-BOPTA+%3D+gadobenate+dimeglumine&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">Gd-BOPTA = gadobenate dimeglumine</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HCC+%3D+hepatocellular+carcinoma&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HCC = hepatocellular carcinoma</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=H-E+%3D+hematoxylineosin&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">H-E = hematoxylineosin</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=NRH+%3D+nodular+regenerative+hyperplasia&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">NRH = nodular regenerative hyperplasia</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SSFP+%3D+steady-state+free+precession&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SSFP = steady-state free precession</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=THID+%3D+transient+hepatic+intensity+difference&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">THID = transient hepatic intensity difference</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">MR imaging features of the more frequently encountered primary and secondary hypervascular liver lesions are discussed and illustrated, with emphasis on the role of advanced MR imaging techniques and hepatocyte-specific contrast agents.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Alvin C.</span> <span property="familyName">Silva</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology (A.C.S., J.M.E., A.K.H.), Department of Laboratory Medicine and Pathology (A.E.M.), Division of Gastroenterology and Hepatology (H.E.V.), and Division of Transplantation Medicine (H.E.V., M.A.J.), Mayo Clinic, 13400 E Shea Blvd, Scottsdale, AZ 85259. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 6, 2008; revision requested Jun